early on is that if you're

00:01:02.027 --> 00:01:07.133
booked on a gig, you better do
your time. No more, no less. Do

00:01:07.166 --> 00:01:10.436
your time. Now when I started
doing comedy, it was in Boston,

00:01:10.469 --> 00:01:13.840
Massachusetts, and when I was
starting out I was just starting

00:01:13.873 --> 00:01:16.776
to work and the way the shows
worked at that time is you do

00:01:16.809 --> 00:01:19.579
road gigs and the first guy
would do a half an hour, the

00:01:19.612 --> 00:01:22.181
headliner would do forty-five
minutes and that was the show.

00:01:22.214 --> 00:01:25.551
So now I'm just starting to open
and there was this dude who

00:01:25.584 --> 00:01:29.188
moved to Boston from Cleveland,
no one knew who he was. All we

00:01:29.221 --> 00:01:31.858
knew was that he didn't like his
name in the paper, he didn't

00:01:31.891 --> 00:01:34.660
want his name on the marquee
because the IRS was after him

00:01:34.693 --> 00:01:39.065
and an ex-wife. So this guy was
actually on the lamb doing live

00:01:39.098 --> 00:01:43.202
stand-up comedy. These are the
kind of people that were around

00:01:43.235 --> 00:01:46.939
doing comedy back in the day.
And this guy's name was Frankie

00:01:46.972 --> 00:01:52.311
Bastille. Now I had to go pick
Frankie up to drive him to a gig

00:01:52.344 --> 00:01:54.714
in Connecticut. We were going to
drive two and a half hours, me

00:01:54.747 --> 00:01:57.150
and this guy I'd never met
before. So I go to this

00:01:57.183 --> 00:01:59.418
apartment building and I'm
walking down this hallway to

00:01:59.451 --> 00:02:02.121
pick this dude up and all I hear
from the end of the hall coming

00:02:02.154 --> 00:02:04.724
from an apartment I can't quite
see is some guy going, "Where's

00:02:04.757 --> 00:02:09.295
my tooth? Where's my fucking
tooth?" And I'm like, "What is

00:02:09.328 --> 00:02:12.865
going on?" And I know on the
door and this dude opens up, he

00:02:12.898 --> 00:02:15.401
looks like Keith Richards and
he's missing his front tooth. He

00:02:15.434 --> 00:02:22.542
goes, "I'm Frankie, I can't find
my tooth." Alright, I'm Marc.

00:02:22.575 --> 00:02:24.544
He's like, "Alright, we gotta
find my tooth and then we go."

00:02:24.577 --> 00:02:26.546
Um, Alright. So we look around
for the tooth for about twenty

00:02:26.579 --> 00:02:28.548
minutes and he reaches into his
pocket and he goes, "Oh shit, I

00:02:28.581 --> 00:02:32.351
got it," and he pops his tooth
into his face. So that was

00:02:32.384 --> 00:02:35.388
Frankie. He had a Tibetan chant
tattooed around one arm, he had

00:02:35.421 --> 00:02:37.390
some other tattoos on the other
arm, he looked like Keith

00:02:37.423 --> 00:02:39.725
Richards and he talked like
that, he's like, "Alright, man,

00:02:39.758 --> 00:02:42.728
